summary: An Ordinance providing for the improvement of North and West Sixtieth Street from Phinney Avenue to the west boundary line of the City of Seattle, by grading and curbing the same, in accordance with Resolution No. 602 of the City Council of the City of Seattle, and providing for the payment therefor by the mode of "Payment by Bonds," as provided by the laws of the State of Washington and the Charter and Ordinances of the City of Seattle
